Tony Okafor, Awka The Anambra State chapter of the Peoples Democratic Party, has sacked three members of its executive for alleged anti-party activities. The state Chairman of the party, Chief Ndubuisi Nwobu, announced this at a meeting of the state Executive Committee in Awka. He said their removal was sequel to their indictment by the state disciplinary committee. He gave the names of those sacked as Emeka Obi (secretary), Marcel Anyiam, Vice Chairman (South) and Callista Adimachukwu (ex-women leader). Nwobu said, “They are replaced by Chief Emmanuel Ebene as Vice-chairman, Okoli Akirika, Secretary; and Mrs Justina Nwafor as women leader. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 